Paper: hep-th/9404087

Date: 1994-04-14

Title: On the physical interpretation of effective actions using Schwinger's

formulaAuthors: L. C. de Albuquerque, C. Farina, Silvio J. Rabello and Arvind N.

VaidyaComments: 5 p., REVTEX, IF-UFRJ-94

Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 34 (1995) 373-377

We show explicitly that Schwinger's formula for one-loop effective actionscorresponds to the summation of energies associated with the zero-pointoscillations of the fields. We begin with a formal proof, and after that weconfirm it using a regularization prescription.